A frustrated traveler standing alone in a vast, sterile airport terminal at night, their silhouette reflected in floor-to-ceiling windows showing parked aircraft. They hold a mobile phone with a cracked, glowing red screen displaying an error symbol. The scene is rendered in a cyberpunk style with harsh neon lighting in cold blues and magentic pinks cutting through the darkness, rain streaking the windows, holographic departure boards flickering overhead, and distant figures moving like ghosts. The traveler's posture conveys isolation and helplessness—shoulders slumped, head bowed slightly toward the useless device. Steam rises from grates in the floor, and abandoned luggage creates geometric shadows. The mood is one of technological betrayal and urban loneliness, emphasizing the disconnect between promised connectivity and reality.
